<div id="pf3b" class="pf w2 h0" data-page-no="3b"><div class="pc pc3b w2 h0"><div class="t m5fa x8b h31 y613 ff7 fs1f fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUNDAY </div><div class="t m5fb x41 h17 y6fc ff2 fsa fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">November 7 </div><div class="t m156 x0 h30 y6fd ff1 fs1e fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Vision </div><div class="t m2a7 xca h8 y596 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Dan. 7:1-8). </div><div class="t m46b x4e h8 y6fe ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In his vision Daniel sees the four winds of heaven stirring up the great </div><div class="t m251 x0 h8 y5e1 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sea. As a result of it, four wild beasts emerge from the water. </div><div class="t m2c5 x33 h31 y5e2 ff7 fs1f fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What </div><div class="t m46b x4e h7 y6ff ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> explanations can we glean from Scripture for most of the symbols </div><div class="t m14d x60 h7 y700 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">appearing in this vision? </div><div class="t m5fc x14 h8 y339 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Winds (Jer. 25:31-33) </div><div class="t m41 xf h8 y701 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m42 x3d h8 y701 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m4d4 x14 h8 y702 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Water (Isa. 57:20, Rev. 17:15) </div><div class="t m41 x41 h8 y703 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m42 x6e h8 y703 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m175 x14 h8 y704 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The four beasts (Dan. 7:17) </div><div class="t m41 x1a h8 y704 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m42 x64 h8 y704 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m252 x60 h8 y705 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lion (Dan. 2:38) </div><div class="t m41 xab h8 y705 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m42 x64 h8 y705 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m1d0 x60 h8 y706 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Bear (Dan. 5:28, 8:20) </div><div class="t m41 x9a h8 y707 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m42 x3d h8 y707 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m1f2 x14 h8 y6ee ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Leopard (Dan. 8:21, 11:2) </div><div class="t m41 x1a h8 y6ee ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m42 x64 h8 y6ee ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m5fd x65 h8 y708 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Any history book about the ancient world will confirm that the great </div><div class="t m497 x14 h8 y709 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">world powers following Babylon were Media-Persia and Greece. But </div><div class="t m4b3 x14 h8 y70a ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">what about the fourth power, the dreadful and terrible beast? Though not </div><div class="t m1fa x14 h8 y70b ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">specifically named in Scripture, history confirms that the power that </div><div class="t m5fe x14 h8 y70c ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">defeated Greece was Rome, the only sensible identification for the fourth </div><div class="t m19b x14 h8 y70d ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">beast. </div><div class="t m2c5 x46 h31 y70e ff7 fs1f fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What </div><div class="t m1cb x65 h7 y70e ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> are the similarities between the expressions used to describe the </div><div class="t md4 x14 h7 y70f ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fourth kingdom in Daniel 2 and the fourth kingdom in Daniel 7? </div><div class="t m259 x14 h8 y710 ff2 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Compare Dan. 2:40 and Dan. 7:7, 23. </div><div class="t m31 x65 h8 y711 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">World power may be said to have passed from the Greeks to the </div><div class="t m30f x14 h8 y712 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Romans at the battle of Pydna, in 168 </div><div class="t m253 x54 h5c y712 ff3 fs26 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">B.C., </div><div class="t m2dd x26 h8 y713 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">where the Romans won a com-</div><div class="t m167 x14 h8 y714 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">plete victory over Macedonia, which was divided into four confederacies </div><div class="t m32f x14 h8 y715 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that eventually became a Roman province. Thus, within another century </div><div class="t m58d x14 h8 y477 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of conquests, the world was united under Rome. History affirms, again, </div><div class="t m393 x14 h8 y478 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God&apos;s foreknowledge of world events. </div><div class="t m5ff x1e h8 y602 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">57 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
